Currently: trying to screw with service node port range
    http://www.thinkcode.se/blog/2019/02/20/kubernetes-service-node-port-range
    I'd like to expose reimu-00 80 for the nginx ingress controller
    Update: seems like this is working out fine -- see below

hakurei: modified node port range to allow 53 (dns), 80
    /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-apiserver.yaml
    --service-node-port-range=50-30000

hakurei: Network change, address got updated from 10.0.100.24 to 10.0.4.65
    Edited /etc/kubernetes/kubelet.conf to point to correct server
    systemctl restart'ed kubelet on hakurei and reimu-00
    Soln: see https://stackoverflow.com/questions/46360361/invalid-x509-certificate-for-kubernetes-master
    Second answer, "kubeadm alpha" doesn't work but comments `kubeadm init phase certs all` does
        I also signed it for "hakurei"
    rm /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf then kubeadm init phase kubeconfig admin
    For some reason reimu-00 is fine with this?

(-1). remove old kubernetes
    sudo kubeadm reset && sudo rm -r /etc/cni/net.d/ && sudo systemctl restart docker
0. kubeadm init on hakurei
    sudo kubeadm init \
      --pod-network-cidr=10.244.0.0/16
1. kubeadm join on reimu-00
    copy/paste
2. edit /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-apiserver.yaml
 echo '*** kube-apiserver.yaml 2021-07-02 21:57:02.719492094 -0700
--- /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-apiserver.yaml       2021-07-02 21:57:33.909492078 -0700
***************
*** 39,44 ****
--- 39,45 ----
      - --service-account-key-file=/etc/kubernetes/pki/sa.pub
      - --service-account-signing-key-file=/etc/kubernetes/pki/sa.key
      - --service-cluster-ip-range=10.96.0.0/12
+     - --service-node-port-range=50-30000
      - --tls-cert-file=/etc/kubernetes/pki/apiserver.crt
      - --tls-private-key-file=/etc/kubernetes/pki/apiserver.key
      image: k8s.gcr.io/kube-apiserver:v1.21.2' | sudo patch /etc/kubernetes/manifests/kube-apiserver.yaml
3. Pull down kubeconf admin
    sudo cat /etc/kubernetes/admin.conf
4. Begin applying terraform
    import post init script if you deleted the tf state
